originalText.text: Don’t return deposits. Moved out October 31st, it is the first week of January and no security deposit returned or intent to claim security deposit. Office keeps saying First Service is delayed due to the holidays. Terrible service!

originalText.text: Arguably the best luxury rental building on the Upper East Side. Most staff members have been with the buildings for over a decade, are courteous, kind, and attentive. Staff delivers packages directly to your door. Driveway round about makes Uber pick ups/drop offs exceptionally easy, and provides safety as it is quite off the street. Apartments are well appointed, well laid out, quiet and comfortable. Before moving in I was concerned with potential noise from the bridge, but this proved to be a non-issue. Perhaps my only complaint are the air handlers, which are not as effective at cooling the apartments during the summer. On average the the units maintain a very comfortable temperatures. Highly recommend this community after 3 years living here, and pray that the new owner does not make substantial changes to what is an exceptionally well managed operation.

originalText.text: I came to tour an apartment and paid my good faith deposit right after the tour, which according to the leasing agent would take the apartment off market. I also later confirmed with the agent on the approval timeline he said he’s trying to get it by that day, and since I should have no issue with the approval based on income and credit, I went ahead to book my movers and bought moving tools. A few hours later the agent called me saying someone else offered a higher rent(which means he didn’t take the apartment off the market) and he’s going to return my deposit. It was a partial deposit and I had to ask for the full amount and they still haven’t paid back that neither my application fee. This turned out to be illegal. Just leaving the experience here so people can watch out in the future. Def not a business that puts integrity as the first and be careful spending your time with them. If they can’t even keep their words before you move in, they definitely can’t after you do.
